I saw it back there. I don't-

356
00:23:19,631 --> 00:23:23,968
Ten-twelve, we got a stranded vehicle
in the vicinity of.

357
00:23:23,968 --> 00:23:28,439
Yeah, we got a white jeep,
license plate three H-E-L five eight one,

358
00:23:28,439 --> 00:23:31,738
registered to a Ryan Edward Dunbar.

359
00:23:32,477 --> 00:23:36,114
Oh, man, Ryan, l- I haven't seen Ryan
since high school.

360
00:23:36,114 --> 00:23:38,016
Well, he and his girlfriend are stuck
in a ditch out about

361
00:23:38,016 --> 00:23:41,247
a mile and a half from twenty-eight
seventy-six Montpelier.

362
00:23:44,022 --> 00:23:45,890
Two eight seven six Montpelier?

363
00:23:45,890 --> 00:23:46,591
That's right.

364
00:23:46,591 --> 00:23:48,422
Did he happen to mention
his girlfriend's name?

365
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,762
Uh, he didn't, no.

366
00:23:50,762 --> 00:23:53,431
Uh, but he said he thought they might
have been involved in a hit and run.

367
00:23:53,431 --> 00:23:55,667
He thought they might have been?

368
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:57,368
That's right. That's what he said.

369
00:23:57,368 --> 00:24:01,005
Um, he thought maybe the other driver
was trying to harm them in some way.

370
00:24:01,005 --> 00:24:01,439
I don't know.

371
00:24:01,439 --> 00:24:04,169
It didn't make a hell of a lot of sense,
