00:48:03,413 --> 00:48:04,981
I will take that sucker apart
and I will put it back together,

764
00:48:04,981 --> 00:48:06,783
and you won't believe how goddamned good
that toast tastes.

765
00:48:06,783 --> 00:48:10,553
Seriously. Seriously.
I swear, man. Seriously.

766
00:48:10,553 --> 00:48:11,354
My toaster's fine.

767
00:48:11,354 --> 00:48:12,378
I'm hot in here.

768
00:48:39,048 --> 00:48:41,151
Mmm, snookers.

769
00:48:41,151 --> 00:48:42,419
Angel cheeks.

770
00:48:42,419 --> 00:48:43,686
You're so pretty.

771
00:48:43,686 --> 00:48:45,355
You're pretty. You're pretty.

772
00:48:45,355 --> 00:48:46,879
You're pretty. You're pretty.

773
00:48:47,557 --> 00:48:48,925
Hey, it's snowing like hell.

774
00:48:48,925 --> 00:48:50,427
Why is it snowing so damn much?

775
00:48:50,427 --> 00:48:54,625
Global warming.
Beautiful, isn't it? Stop it.

776
00:49:25,795 --> 00:49:28,398
And it was your impression that
she'd never done it before?

777
00:49:28,398 --> 00:49:31,026
That's how it looked to me. Him too.

778
00:49:31,868 --> 00:49:33,236
So why didn't you warn them?

779
00:49:33,236 --> 00:49:34,931
Warn them about what?

780
00:49:35,505 --> 00:49:37,841
All right, I told you, let me be alone.
Jeez.

781
00:49:37,841 --> 00:49:40,241
Well, you must have known that
they were doing too much.

782
00:49:40,810 --> 00:49:43,643
You definitely knew that
there was a blizzard outside.

783
00:49:44,714 --> 00:49:46,181
So why didn't you tell them not to leave?

784
00:49:47,750 --> 00:49:50,048
Well, I tried. We all did.

785
00:49:51,087 --> 00:49:52,054
But they wouldn't listen.

786
00:49:53,289 --> 00:49:57,749
So we just packed them a little
something for the road and off they went.

787
00:49:58,828 --> 00:50:00,159
You mean that you gave them some more?

788
00:50:01,931 --> 00:50:03,523
We figured it was a friendly thing to do.

789
00:50:27,991 --> 00:50:30,193
Nine-one-one emergency.

790
00:50:30,193 --> 00:50:31,694
They got my kid.

791
00:50:31,694 --> 00:50:32,962
I'm sorry?

792
00:50:32,962 --> 00:50:33,897
The skinheads.

793
00:50:33,897 --> 00:50:35,598
They're torturing people.

794
00:50:35,598 --> 00:50:36,966
They almost got me and Shelley.

795
00:50:36,966 --> 00:50:38,067
Ryan, is that you?

796
00:50:38,067 --> 00:50:40,236
I can barely hear you.
You got to speak up.

797
00:50:40,236 --> 00:50:42,005
Okay. They might hear me.

798
00:50:42,005 --> 00:50:43,206
Who might hear you?

799
00:50:43,206 --> 00:50:45,141
The skinheads.

800
00:50:45,141 --> 00:50:46,175
They're all around us.

801
00:50:46,175 --> 00:50:48,111
You mean all around the truck?

802
00:50:48,111 --> 00:50:50,446
No. We're not in the truck.

803
00:50:50,446 --> 00:50:53,550
Ryan, you're not outside, are you?

804
00:50:53,550 --> 00:50:56,386
You can't be outside.
You'll freeze to death.

805
00:50:56,386 --> 00:50:59,150
We can't move. They have us trapped.

806
00:50:59,722 --> 00:51:01,824
Ryan, listen to me very carefully.

807
00:51:01,824 --> 00:51:04,060
Nobody's got you trapped.
You're imagining things.

808
00:51:04,060 --> 00:51:07,530
No. No. No. No, no, we saw them.

809
00:51:07,530 --> 00:51:09,499
They were- they were torturing people.

810
00:51:09,499 --> 00:51:12,068
They almost got Shelley.

811
00:51:12,068 --> 00:51:14,704
Where is Shelley?
Can I speak to Shelley please?

812
00:51:14,704 --> 00:51:19,108
Shh. Hey. Hey.
They want to talk to you.

813
00:51:19,108 --> 00:51:21,344
You think you can?

814
00:51:21,344 --> 00:51:23,012
Okay. Hello?

815
00:51:23,012 --> 00:51:24,647
Shelley.

816
00:51:24,647 --> 00:51:26,616
You guys have got to get back
in the truck and stay there.

817
00:51:26,616 --> 00:51:29,252
Do you understand?
We spoke to Ryan's cell phone company.

818
00:51:29,252 --> 00:51:32,188
It looks like he's got
his GPS turned off.

819
00:51:32,188 --> 00:51:33,256
Why- I don't- what? What?

820
00:51:33,256 --> 00:51:34,324
GPS.

821
00:51:34,324 --> 00:51:35,224
Help the cell phone company trace...

822
00:51:35,224 --> 00:51:39,718
Please, send somebody to get us.
Cold. Please.

823
00:51:40,330 --> 00:51:41,497
Skinheads?

824
00:51:41,497 --> 00:51:42,765
That's what they said.

825
00:51:42,765 --> 00:51:46,302
But they promised they would get back
inside the truck and stay there.

826
00:51:46,302 --> 00:51:47,804
Who'd you speak to, him or her?

827
00:51:47,804 --> 00:51:49,396
Both.

828
00:51:49,906 --> 00:51:51,307
How'd she sound?

829
00:51:51,307 --> 00:51:54,834
Pretty coherent,
considering how much she's done.

830
00:52:08,758 --> 00:52:09,926
Shelley?

831
00:52:09,926 --> 00:52:12,258
It's me. I got bad news.

832
00:52:12,729 --> 00:52:16,529
Shelley's on drugs and she's running
around outside in the snow.

833
00:52:38,588 --> 00:52:40,351
It's not there!

834
00:52:42,792 --> 00:52:45,028
Someone took my car away.

835
00:52:45,028 --> 00:52:47,030
Are you sure that's where it was?

836
00:52:47,030 --> 00:52:48,731
Yeah, yeah, pretty sure.

837
00:52:48,731 --> 00:52:50,700
They must have dragged it out of
the ditch and taken it away.

838
00:52:50,700 --> 00:52:52,395
Larry?

839
00:52:53,336 --> 00:52:54,137
What was that?

840
00:52:54,137 --> 00:52:54,971
What? What?

841
00:52:54,971 --> 00:52:58,634
Shelley, are you out here? Answer me!

842
00:53:00,243 --> 00:53:00,677
Mom, you--

843
00:53:00,677 --> 00:53:03,112
What in the world do you
think you're doing?

844
00:53:03,112 --> 00:53:05,910
I've been worried half to death.

845
00:53:06,249 --> 00:53:08,518
Mom, you can walk!

846
00:53:08,518 --> 00:53:10,153
Well, of course I'm walking fine.

847
00:53:10,153 --> 00:53:12,417
I always could.

848
00:53:13,256 --> 00:53:15,024
I was going to walk right out of this town,

849
00:53:15,024 --> 00:53:16,559
but then I got pregnant with you, and--

850
00:53:16,559 --> 00:53:19,762
You were faking to keep me here
this whole time?

851
00:53:19,762 --> 00:53:21,898
Well, you kept me here.

852
00:53:21,898 --> 00:53:24,901
You think I've never had
any dreams of my own?

853
00:53:24,901 --> 00:53:28,971
So why shouldn't I strand you
the way you stranded me?

854
00:53:28,971 --> 00:53:32,372
You bitch! I'll kill you!

855
00:53:39,816 --> 00:53:41,584
No, Shelley! Shelley, relax!

856
00:53:41,584 --> 00:53:42,819
Hey! Hey!

857
00:53:42,819 --> 00:53:44,387
It's me!
Who were you talking to?

858
00:53:44,387 --> 00:53:45,822
My mother.

859
00:53:45,822 --> 00:53:46,622
What?

860
00:53:46,622 --> 00:53:48,988
Ryan, she lied.

861
00:53:51,294 --> 00:53:52,161
Calm down.

862
00:53:52,161 --> 00:53:54,630
Hey, hey! I think I found the car.

863
00:53:54,630 --> 00:53:57,100
It's right over there.
It's going to be okay.

864
00:53:57,100 --> 00:53:58,624
All right?

865
00:54:16,786 --> 00:54:19,346
I've got them. I've got the truck.

866
00:54:37,673 --> 00:54:39,834
Shelley!

867
00:54:41,344 --> 00:54:43,403
Shelley!

868
00:54:52,955 --> 00:54:55,116
That's not your car.

869
00:54:55,792 --> 00:54:58,194
You think anybody lives here?

870
00:54:58,194 --> 00:55:00,185
Would you?

871
00:55:03,933 --> 00:55:08,271
Hello in there! Hello?

872
00:55:08,271 --> 00:55:10,603
Hello?

873
00:55:29,025 --> 00:55:31,084
Come on. Oh...

874
00:55:36,332 --> 00:55:38,129
Whoa.

875
00:55:51,747 --> 00:55:52,515
It's a kitchen.

876
00:55:52,515 --> 00:55:53,982
Yeah.

877
00:57:19,435 --> 00:57:21,426
Come on. Help me out.

878
00:57:36,185 --> 00:57:37,553
Give me your, uh, your lighter.

879
00:57:37,553 --> 00:57:39,214
Yeah. Hold on.

880
00:57:41,891 --> 00:57:43,426
Ryan, I can't find it.

881
00:57:43,426 --> 00:57:44,727
Oh, come on, don't tell me you lost it.

882
00:57:44,727 --> 00:57:46,786
Didn't you see me with it?

883
00:57:48,965 --> 00:57:51,000
Ha. There.

884
00:57:51,000 --> 00:57:52,934
Come on, turn.

885
00:57:58,074 --> 00:57:59,642
Maybe it's.

886
00:57:59,642 --> 00:58:01,337
Dammed.

887
00:58:04,347 --> 00:58:06,076
It's okay.

888
00:58:16,359 --> 00:58:18,156
What is it?

889
00:58:33,442 --> 00:58:34,577
It's about time.

890
00:58:34,577 --> 00:58:36,212
Is Eliot okay? Is he there with you?

891
00:58:36,212 --> 00:58:37,046
Eliot?

892
00:58:37,046 --> 00:58:38,514
Since when did you ever
give a damn about Eliot?

893
00:58:38,514 --> 00:58:39,682
Come on, is he there with you or not?

894
00:58:39,682 --> 00:58:41,851
Yes, of course.

895
00:58:41,851 --> 00:58:43,652
And do you know where we are?

896
00:58:43,652 --> 00:58:44,720
Your place.

897
00:58:44,720 --> 00:58:47,356
Hey, you wouldn't answer your phone
so I came over looking for you.

898
00:58:47,356 --> 00:58:49,859
And you'll never guess who stopped up.

899
00:58:49,859 --> 00:58:50,493
Who?

900
00:58:50,493 --> 00:58:52,862
Bruce Davis, that's who.

901
00:58:52,862 --> 00:58:55,197
And he's a deputy sheriff now.

902
00:58:55,197 --> 00:58:56,599
And he arrested Wade.

903
00:58:56,599 --> 00:58:57,867
What for?

904
00:58:57,867 --> 00:59:00,165
Possession.

905
00:59:01,037 --> 00:59:04,573
I thought he was going to
arrest me too, but he didn't.

906
00:59:04,573 --> 00:59:08,044
But he is going to haul your ass in
as soon as they find you.

907
00:59:08,044 --> 00:59:10,246
What- what- wait- wait- what- what for?
What did I do?

908
00:59:10,246 --> 00:59:12,481
Well, it's your trailer too, right?

909
00:59:12,481 --> 00:59:18,010
You're both going down for possession,
and I couldn't be happier.

910
00:59:19,588 --> 00:59:21,021
Hello?

911
00:59:21,924 --> 00:59:23,926
Hello?

912
00:59:23,926 --> 00:59:27,521
Ryan,
I know you did not just hang up on me.

913
00:59:29,665 --> 00:59:31,360
I'm in trouble.

914
00:59:32,201 --> 00:59:34,465
Why- why? What do you mean?

915
01:00:05,434 --> 01:00:07,561
I'm not getting any answer.

916
01:00:08,070 --> 01:00:09,738
The phone's gone dead?

917
01:00:09,738 --> 01:00:10,773
Well, it's ringing,

918
01:00:10,773 --> 01:00:14,110
and usually when a phone goes dead
it goes straight to voice mail.

919
01:00:14,110 --> 01:00:16,670
And he never turned on his GPS?

920
01:00:17,480 --> 01:00:19,181
I'll check again with
his cell phone company,

921
01:00:19,181 --> 01:00:21,843
but no, I don't think he ever did.

922
01:00:23,219 --> 01:00:24,887
Ready?

923
01:00:24,887 --> 01:00:28,724
Yeah.
I- I really appreciate this, Larry.

924
01:00:28,724 --> 01:00:32,328
Know. You know what?
We're going to find her.

925
01:00:32,328 --> 01:00:33,727
Okay.

926
01:01:15,771 --> 01:01:17,432
Mm.

927
01:01:20,609 --> 01:01:22,804
You want some?

928
01:01:24,313 --> 01:01:25,881
Well, I am. May as well.

929
01:01:25,881 --> 01:01:27,940
I'm going to jail anyway.

930
01:01:28,551 --> 01:01:29,785
No.

931
01:01:29,785 --> 01:01:34,051
I'm not going to let them take you
somewhere I can't be with you.

932
01:01:34,523 --> 01:01:37,287
You really do love me, don't you?

933
01:01:37,993 --> 01:01:40,257
You have to ask?

934
01:01:41,263 --> 01:01:43,799
I guess a small part of me
never believed it.

935
01:01:43,799 --> 01:01:47,169
I mean, come on, you're just so perfect,
and I'm- I'm a screw up.

936
01:01:47,169 --> 01:01:49,933
I am so not perfect.

937
01:01:50,372 --> 01:01:53,075
That was the problem with me and Keith,
you know?

938
01:01:53,075 --> 01:01:57,535
He was perfect. I was just bored.

939
01:01:58,480 --> 01:02:00,616
I needed trouble, Ryan Dunbar.

940
01:02:00,616 --> 01:02:03,219
Trouble? I gave you that.

941
01:02:03,219 --> 01:02:06,916
Oh, trouble's not the right word.

942
01:02:08,324 --> 01:02:10,926
I needed excitement, you know?

943
01:02:10,926 --> 01:02:14,196
Something, anything, just to feel alive.

944
01:02:14,196 --> 01:02:16,630
Yeah, tell me about it.

945
01:02:17,499 --> 01:02:21,629
Why can't they just leave us alone?
You know?

946
01:02:22,471 --> 01:02:28,611
I love you, you love me,
should be simple, right?

947
01:02:28,611 --> 01:02:29,845
But no.

948
01:02:29,845 --> 01:02:33,212
Ever since we go together
they've been trying to break us up.

949
01:02:34,683 --> 01:02:36,018
I mean, marriages break up.

950
01:02:36,018 --> 01:02:37,486
What's the big deal?

951
01:02:37,486 --> 01:02:38,721
Especially if they're mistakes
to begin with.

952
01:02:38,721 --> 01:02:40,823
Exactly.

953
01:02:40,823 --> 01:02:45,094
Why can't they just live
their lives and let us be happy?

954
01:02:45,094 --> 01:02:46,662
They're jealous.

955
01:02:46,662 --> 01:02:47,529
Oh yeah?

956
01:02:47,529 --> 01:02:48,163
Yeah.

957
01:02:48,163 --> 01:02:49,531
Of what?

958
01:02:49,531 --> 01:02:53,262
Because you and I haven't given up,
like they have.

959
01:02:55,938 --> 01:02:57,473
Is that the sheriff?

960
01:02:57,473 --> 01:02:58,474
That's got to be the sheriff.

961
01:02:58,474 --> 01:03:00,909
Ryan, we have to answer that.

962
01:03:00,909 --> 01:03:01,510
Hello?

963
01:03:01,510 --> 01:03:04,179
Shelley?
Thank god, I thought you were dead.

964
01:03:04,179 --> 01:03:05,714
You're not taking Ryan away from me.

965
01:03:05,714 --> 01:03:07,739
Nobody said they were.

966
01:03:08,384 --> 01:03:11,387
I swear, just tell me where you are.

967
01:03:11,387 --> 01:03:13,822
Tell me that you're someplace safe,
inside.

968
01:03:13,822 --> 01:03:16,592
We're- we're out in those camps,

969
01:03:16,592 --> 01:03:19,495
where people take their kids out
in the country.

970
01:03:19,495 --> 01:03:20,229
Inside?

971
01:03:20,229 --> 01:03:22,131
Yeah. But there's no heat.

972
01:03:22,131 --> 01:03:24,900
There's a fireplace,
but we can't get a fire started.

973
01:03:24,900 --> 01:03:27,069
That's all she said, they're in a camp?

974
01:03:27,069 --> 01:03:29,538
There's at least ten of those places
in this county alone.

975
01:03:29,538 --> 01:03:31,273
Well, she also said
there was a van outside.

976
01:03:31,273 --> 01:03:33,475
Does that help at all?

977
01:03:33,475 --> 01:03:34,476
Not really.

978
01:03:34,476 --> 01:03:36,478
They can't have gotten that far on foot,

979
01:03:36,478 --> 01:03:39,648
and the truck is...
where'd you find it again?

980
01:03:39,648 --> 01:03:41,250
Meridian Way. Out.

981
01:03:41,250 --> 01:03:41,917
You heard that, right?

982
01:03:41,917 --> 01:03:43,111
Yep. Hang on.

983
01:03:49,725 --> 01:03:51,193
We're not going to get stuck, are we?

984
01:03:51,193 --> 01:03:52,785
Don't worry about it.

985
01:03:59,134 --> 01:04:00,569
Frank Van nick.

986
01:04:00,569 --> 01:04:01,537
What?

987
01:04:01,537 --> 01:04:02,738
Do you remember Frank Van nick?

988
01:04:02,738 --> 01:04:05,741
He- the guy who used to be the bartender
at The Red Line a few years back?

989
01:04:05,741 --> 01:04:06,608
He's bald, kind of stocky?

990
01:04:06,608 --> 01:04:07,876
Used to come on to you quite a bit?

991
01:04:07,876 --> 01:04:08,877
Yeah, he did.

992
01:04:08,877 --> 01:04:09,978
And you used to encourage him?

993
01:04:09,978 --> 01:04:10,879
No, I didn't.

994
01:04:10,879 --> 01:04:11,814
Yeah, you did.

995
01:04:11,814 --> 01:04:13,682
Uh, can we not get into this?

996
01:04:13,682 --> 01:04:14,750
Did you sleep with him?

997
01:04:14,750 --> 01:04:17,152
No, but I think he had a van.
Didn't he?

998
01:04:17,152 --> 01:04:18,220
I have no idea.

999
01:04:18,220 --> 01:04:19,722
No, remember? He had a van.

1000
01:04:19,722 --> 01:04:21,223
It used to break down all the time.

1001
01:04:21,223 --> 01:04:22,925
I think he got a job out
at Camp Castanoan,

1002
01:04:22,925 --> 01:04:24,593
and he was a caretaker or something.

1003
01:04:24,593 --> 01:04:25,861
How- how many times
did you sleep with him?

1004
01:04:25,861 --> 01:04:26,895
I didn't sleep with him.

1005
01:04:26,895 --> 01:04:28,197
But I think that's where they are.

1006
01:04:28,197 --> 01:04:30,566
I bet they're at Camp Castanoan.

1007
01:04:30,566 --> 01:04:31,767
Can I use your phone?

1008
01:04:31,767 --> 01:04:32,968
Why, so you can call him?

1009
01:04:32,968 --> 01:04:36,267
No, smart ass, so I can call the sheriff.

1010
01:04:56,959 --> 01:04:58,460
What was that?

1011
01:04:58,460 --> 01:05:00,155
Let me see.

1012
01:05:03,932 --> 01:05:06,366
No, no, no, no, just stay there.
Stay there.

1013
01:05:24,887 --> 01:05:27,355
We're surrounded!
We got to get out of here! Come on!

1014
01:05:42,604 --> 01:05:43,238
Oh, no.

1015
01:05:43,238 --> 01:05:44,227
Oh!

1016
01:05:45,674 --> 01:05:48,142
Freeze! You're under arrest.

1017
01:05:49,912 --> 01:05:51,413
Bruce! Hush.

1018
01:05:51,413 --> 01:05:54,246
Bruce, oh my god,
I'm so glad to see you.

1019
01:05:55,317 --> 01:05:56,750
Shot!

1020
01:05:57,286 --> 01:06:00,687
Ryan, baby, baby! Baby!

1021
01:06:01,089 --> 01:06:02,925
No. No. No.

1022
01:06:02,925 --> 01:06:06,728
Look, you see?
You see what you did to me?

1023
01:06:06,728 --> 01:06:08,630
No. No. No!

1024
01:06:08,630 --> 01:06:11,121
Shelley! Hey! Come on!

1025
01:06:16,772 --> 01:06:17,773
What? oh! No! Did to me!

1026
01:06:17,773 --> 01:06:20,309
No! Ryan! Ryan!

1027
01:06:20,309 --> 01:06:21,970
Look, you see?

1028
01:08:35,077 --> 01:08:35,777
Did you find her?

1029
01:08:35,777 --> 01:08:36,712
No.

1030
01:08:36,712 --> 01:08:38,447
They were here,
but they're not here now.

1031
01:08:38,447 --> 01:08:41,780
Oh my god. Oh my god.

1032
01:08:42,050 --> 01:08:42,584
Don't panic.

1033
01:08:42,584 --> 01:08:43,819
She's been drinking.

1034
01:08:43,819 --> 01:08:46,421
Shut up!
My daughter's going to freeze to death

1035
01:08:46,421 --> 01:08:48,490
and you're giving me crap about drinking?

1036
01:08:48,490 --> 01:08:49,691
Geez, why would they leave?

1037
01:08:49,691 --> 01:08:52,661
I don't know, but they're on foot
so they couldn't have gotten far.

1038
01:08:52,661 --> 01:08:54,196
Yeah.
This is all my fault.

1039
01:08:54,196 --> 01:08:55,497
You know,
you're really not helping, Gayle.

1040
01:08:55,497 --> 01:08:58,200
You have no idea what I'm going through.

1041
01:08:58,200 --> 01:09:00,035
I know better than you do, Gayle.

1042
01:09:00,035 --> 01:09:01,803
You know what else?

1043
01:09:01,803 --> 01:09:03,828
This is your fault.

1044
01:09:05,073 --> 01:09:08,276
She wouldn't be in this mess
if she'd stayed with me.

1045
01:09:08,276 --> 01:09:12,214
You were the one
that came between me and Shelley.

1046
01:09:12,214 --> 01:09:14,850
You did everything
you could to break us up.

1047
01:09:14,850 --> 01:09:17,478
You did everything you could.

1048
01:09:20,288 --> 01:09:21,778
Sorry.

1049
01:09:31,800 --> 01:09:33,791
I like that kid.

1050
01:09:43,512 --> 01:09:45,241
Give me a second.

1051
01:09:46,481 --> 01:09:48,813
Just give me a second.

1052
01:09:49,084 --> 01:09:49,618
I'm burning up.

1053
01:09:49,618 --> 01:09:52,781
Suddenly... so tired.

1054
01:09:54,156 --> 01:09:56,181
Have no choice.

1055
01:09:57,826 --> 01:09:59,561
You lied to us.

1056
01:09:59,561 --> 01:10:00,395
I'm sorry?

1057
01:10:00,395 --> 01:10:02,531
You said you weren't going to arrest me,
but you are.

1058
01:10:02,531 --> 01:10:03,832
You're with them.

1059
01:10:03,832 --> 01:10:04,900
With who?

1060
01:10:04,900 --> 01:10:08,170
The skinheads, my wife,
Bruce, you're all in this together.

1061
01:10:08,170 --> 01:10:08,970
Ryan, listen to me.

1062
01:10:08,970 --> 01:10:11,406
No! You listen to me.

1063
01:10:11,406 --> 01:10:13,575
We do not need your help anymore.

1064
01:10:13,575 --> 01:10:14,242
We'll find our way out ourselves.

1065
01:10:14,242 --> 01:10:17,212
Ryan, please, we're just trying to get
the state to[unintelligible].

1066
01:10:17,212 --> 01:10:19,407
Don't call anymore.

1067
01:10:32,994 --> 01:10:35,397
Hey. Hey. Hey.

1068
01:10:35,397 --> 01:10:36,331
Hey, come on.

1069
01:10:36,331 --> 01:10:38,834
No, Ryan. I need to sleep.

1070
01:10:38,834 --> 01:10:40,435
I want to sleep.

1071
01:10:40,435 --> 01:10:43,305
I know. I do, okay.

1072
01:10:43,305 --> 01:10:44,239
We can't sleep.

1073
01:10:44,239 --> 01:10:45,373
They're going to find us.

1074
01:10:45,373 --> 01:10:46,675
Just a little longer. No.

1075
01:10:46,675 --> 01:10:47,242
Come on.

1076
01:10:47,242 --> 01:10:47,876
Ryan, there's snow up here.
There's more.

1077
01:10:47,876 --> 01:10:54,049
Come on. Come on. Come on. Come on.
Come on. Come on. I got you.

1078
01:10:54,049 --> 01:10:58,754
Just...
Okay. Just trust me.

1079
01:10:58,754 --> 01:11:00,688
I'll get you out of here.

1080
01:11:02,791 --> 01:11:04,860
Come on. Come on.

1081
01:11:04,860 --> 01:11:09,456
Just help me out.
Stand up. Almost done.

1082
01:11:12,067 --> 01:11:14,536
He's right, you know.

1083
01:11:14,536 --> 01:11:16,766
Who's right?

1084
01:11:17,339 --> 01:11:21,143
Bruce.
I did come between him and Shelley.

1085
01:11:21,143 --> 01:11:23,612
I'm the one who set her up with Keith.

1086
01:11:23,612 --> 01:11:26,815
Yeah, I remember.
Never quite understand that one.

1087
01:11:26,815 --> 01:11:29,551
I mean, Keith was a -- well,

1088
01:11:29,551 --> 01:11:32,320
Let’s just say he wasn't exactly
going to set the world on fire.

1089
01:11:32,320 --> 01:11:35,123
Exactly. He wasn't going anywhere.

1090
01:11:35,123 --> 01:11:37,785
Just a small town boy, you know?

1091
01:11:38,059 --> 01:11:41,296
But with Bruce, Shelley had him wrapped
around her little finger,

1092
01:11:41,296 --> 01:11:46,134
and l... guess I was afraid one day
she'd talk him into leaving.

1093
01:11:46,134 --> 01:11:51,439
So yeah, I did everything
I could to break them up.

1094
01:11:51,439 --> 01:11:54,067
You're that scared of losing her.

1095
01:11:55,510 --> 01:11:57,946
She's all I have.

1096
01:11:57,946 --> 01:12:00,081
Well, you still have her.

1097
01:12:00,081 --> 01:12:02,242
I hope.

1098
01:12:04,019 --> 01:12:06,588
You had me too, you know.

1099
01:12:06,588 --> 01:12:08,890
I loved you, Gayle.

1100
01:12:08,890 --> 01:12:11,760
Guess in a kind of strange way,
I still do.

1101
01:12:11,760 --> 01:12:13,895
But you threw me away.

1102
01:12:13,895 --> 01:12:16,031
You didn't want to be with me.
Not after the accident.

1103
01:12:16,031 --> 01:12:18,099
That's a lie and you know it.

1104
01:12:18,099 --> 01:12:19,501
It didn't matter to me.

1105
01:12:19,501 --> 01:12:22,493
I would have stayed with you
no matter what.

1106
01:12:24,973 --> 01:12:26,741
I know.

1107
01:12:26,741 --> 01:12:29,266
So then why?

1108
01:12:30,612 --> 01:12:33,014
Shelley.

1109
01:12:33,014 --> 01:12:36,585
As long as I had you,
she knew she could leave.

1110
01:12:36,585 --> 01:12:38,086
You know,
I had someone to take care of me.

1111
01:12:38,086 --> 01:12:39,888
If I didn't have you...

1112
01:12:39,888 --> 01:12:42,356
Then she'd have to stick around.

1113
01:12:43,225 --> 01:12:46,786
That's how badly
I wanted to hang on to her.

1114
01:12:48,730 --> 01:12:50,332
I've never admitted this to anyone.

1115
01:12:50,332 --> 01:12:52,367
May- probably not even myself.

1116
01:12:52,367 --> 01:12:55,937
But, after the accident,

1117
01:12:55,937 --> 01:12:59,998
I think I knew I'd found a way
to keep her with me.

1118
01:13:01,543 --> 01:13:04,479
I always figured that's what happened.

1119
01:13:04,479 --> 01:13:06,344
I'm sorry.

1120
01:13:11,253 --> 01:13:13,585
Well, it stopped snowing.

1121
01:13:21,563 --> 01:13:30,005
Rest ye merry cheating wives,
and nothing you dismay.

1122
01:13:30,005 --> 01:13:38,470
For that won't be a problem
if you never would have strayed.

1123
01:13:54,429 --> 01:13:55,163
Look out!

1124
01:13:55,163 --> 01:13:57,265
I'm looking! I'm- I'm- I'm looking.

1125
01:13:57,265 --> 01:14:00,068
No, you're not. You're exhausted.

1126
01:14:00,068 --> 01:14:02,737
Come on,
we're getting loaded up on coffee.

1127
01:14:02,737 --> 01:14:07,071
Yeah? Your place or mine?

1128
01:14:08,043 --> 01:14:09,772
Neither.

1129
01:14:39,074 --> 01:14:40,803
I'm so hot.

1130
01:14:41,810 --> 01:14:45,075
Yeah. Yeah, me too.

1131
01:14:50,819 --> 01:14:53,310
Okay. Okay.

1132
01:14:53,655 --> 01:14:54,622
Ryan?

1133
01:14:54,622 --> 01:14:55,557
Hey.

1134
01:14:55,557 --> 01:14:57,286
Ryan?

1135
01:14:58,326 --> 01:15:00,760
Will you marry me?

1136
01:15:01,896 --> 01:15:05,354
Of course. Of course.

1137
01:15:05,834 --> 01:15:08,394
No, I mean now.

1138
01:15:08,703 --> 01:15:10,572
We don't need anybody to tell us
we're married,

1139
01:15:10,572 --> 01:15:13,006
just as long as we believe it.

1140
01:15:15,443 --> 01:15:19,072
Then- then we're married.

1141
01:15:19,381 --> 01:15:23,084
Okay. Come on. Okay.

1142
01:15:23,084 --> 01:15:24,853
I don't want to die in--
Come on.

1143
01:15:24,853 --> 01:15:26,454
What? No.

1144
01:15:26,454 --> 01:15:28,023
No, you're not going to die.

1145
01:15:28,023 --> 01:15:29,650
You're not going to die.

1146
01:15:31,393 --> 01:15:34,362
But I'll die a married woman.

1147
01:15:40,468 --> 01:15:41,302
Wait!

1148
01:15:41,302 --> 01:15:43,668
Oh! Come on. Come on.

1149
01:15:51,646 --> 01:15:52,447
Hold- hold on.

1150
01:15:52,447 --> 01:15:55,283
Hey! Hey, look! Look, it's a house!

1151
01:15:55,283 --> 01:15:58,186
You see it? Oh, we're saved!

1152
01:15:58,186 --> 01:15:59,721
Ryan, Ryan, Ryan.

1153
01:15:59,721 --> 01:16:01,022
We don't know who's in that house, okay?

1154
01:16:01,022 --> 01:16:02,090
They could be waiting for us.

1155
01:16:02,090 --> 01:16:03,591
They could be waiting to kill us.

1156
01:16:03,591 --> 01:16:05,927
No. No. I'm going to go check it out.

1157
01:16:05,927 --> 01:16:08,496
I'm going to check it out.
And- and- and when I come back,

1158
01:16:08,496 --> 01:16:10,726
if it's safe I'm going to get you.

1159
01:16:11,232 --> 01:16:11,633
What?

1160
01:16:11,633 --> 01:16:15,303
No, just- give me your phone,
and, and call me if it's safe.

1161
01:16:15,303 --> 01:16:16,235
Okay.

1162
01:16:56,044 --> 01:16:57,479
Lynn, what's happening?

1163
01:16:57,479 --> 01:16:58,413
We spoke to state.

1164
01:16:58,413 --> 01:17:01,116
We might be able to get some search and
rescue teams out there in about an hour.

1165
01:17:01,116 --> 01:17:03,084
An hour? They can't get
anybody sooner than that?

1166
01:17:03,084 --> 01:17:04,252
I tried to get them sooner.

1167
01:17:04,252 --> 01:17:06,087
That's the best they could do.

1168
01:17:06,087 --> 01:17:07,989
And Shelley hasn't called you?

1169
01:17:07,989 --> 01:17:09,524
I think they turned
their phones off again.

1170
01:17:09,524 --> 01:17:11,526
They haven't picked up
the last few times I called.

1171
01:17:11,526 --> 01:17:13,460
What's the number?

1172
01:17:19,601 --> 01:17:22,126
Ow. Oh.

1173
01:17:31,579 --> 01:17:32,944
Oh.

1174
01:17:36,317 --> 01:17:37,909
No.

1175
01:17:40,922 --> 01:17:42,891
Ryan! Is it safe?

1176
01:17:42,891 --> 01:17:44,759
Shelley, it's Bruce.

1177
01:17:44,759 --> 01:17:47,996
Oh. Why are you calling Ryan's phone?

1178
01:17:47,996 --> 01:17:50,198
I can't- I can't wait- I can't tell you

1179
01:17:50,198 --> 01:17:52,500
how happy I am to hear your voice,
Shelley.

1180
01:17:52,500 --> 01:17:53,301
Where are you?

1181
01:17:53,301 --> 01:17:55,403
I'm- I'm- um, we found a house,

1182
01:17:55,403 --> 01:17:57,705
and I'm waiting for Ryan
to see if it's safe.

1183
01:17:57,705 --> 01:17:59,274
He left you there alone?

1184
01:17:59,274 --> 01:18:04,234
He had to. There are all these people
chasing after us, Bruce.

1185
01:18:05,313 --> 01:18:07,782
He's the one that
you need to worry about.

1186
01:18:07,782 --> 01:18:11,019
You would not be in this position
if it wasn't for him.

1187
01:18:11,019 --> 01:18:12,820
You don't know what you're talking about.

1188
01:18:12,820 --> 01:18:15,490
No, I know that I love you, Shelley.

1189
01:18:15,490 --> 01:18:18,050
I know that I've always loved you.

1190
01:18:20,128 --> 01:18:23,932
I thought that if I went away,
that I'd stop thinking about you.

1191
01:18:23,932 --> 01:18:26,196
But I never did.

1192
01:18:27,202 --> 01:18:31,070
And I've been looking for you
for a long time before tonight.

1193
01:18:32,507 --> 01:18:33,541
It's too late.

1194
01:18:33,541 --> 01:18:35,566
It's not too late.

1195
01:18:36,144 --> 01:18:38,580
I'm going to find you.

1196
01:18:38,580 --> 01:18:42,016
I'm going to find you,
and I'm going to take care of you.

1197
01:18:42,483 --> 01:18:45,153
Whatever you want me to be, I'll be.

1198
01:18:45,153 --> 01:18:47,822
You want to leave this place,
then we'll leave.

1199
01:18:47,822 --> 01:18:49,691
I'm not going anywhere without Ryan.

1200
01:18:49,691 --> 01:18:52,894
But you deserve
so much better than that!

1201
01:18:52,894 --> 01:18:55,920
Few years ago you wouldn't
have gone near him.

1202
01:18:56,464 --> 01:18:58,299
I was a different person then, Bruce.

1203
01:18:58,299 --> 01:19:02,937
That person died.
Everything dies in this town.

1204
01:19:02,937 --> 01:19:05,440
Ryan brought me back to life again.

1205
01:19:05,440 --> 01:19:07,642
Shelley!

1206
01:19:07,642 --> 01:19:09,777
Come here, Shelley! It's okay!

1207
01:19:09,777 --> 01:19:11,312
There's somebody calling.

1208
01:19:11,312 --> 01:19:12,880
Who?

1209
01:19:12,880 --> 01:19:13,681
I can't tell.

1210
01:19:13,681 --> 01:19:17,276
Shelley, it's okay! Ryan's with me.

1211
01:19:17,585 --> 01:19:19,420
Oh, Bruce, I got to go.

1212
01:19:19,420 --> 01:19:20,722
Shelley, stay on the phone!

1213
01:19:20,722 --> 01:19:22,056
Don't hang up. Just stay with me.

1214
01:19:22,056 --> 01:19:23,524
It's okay, Ryan's safe.

1215
01:19:23,524 --> 01:19:24,559
Shelley, don't you understand?

1216
01:19:24,559 --> 01:19:26,857
He's never going to be safe.

1217
01:19:28,029 --> 01:19:30,657
'Course I know. That's why I love him.

1218
01:19:58,459 --> 01:20:00,484
Shelley!

1219
01:20:00,828 --> 01:20:03,661
Come here, Shelley! It's okay!

1220
01:20:22,850 --> 01:20:25,045
Miranda.

1221
01:20:31,793 --> 01:20:34,227
It's okay.

1222
01:20:35,496 --> 01:20:36,097
You're bleeding!

1223
01:20:36,097 --> 01:20:37,530
It's okay.

1224
01:20:39,233 --> 01:20:40,902
How's Ryan? Is he safe?

1225
01:20:40,902 --> 01:20:42,737
Come here. Yeah, he's inside.

1226
01:20:42,737 --> 01:20:47,674
I was lying in bed, and-- oh no!
Oh, god.

1227
01:20:48,710 --> 01:20:50,439
I was lying in bed, and.

1228
01:20:58,319 --> 01:20:59,387
Poor baby.

1229
01:20:59,387 --> 01:21:03,458
He walked in, sat down,
and a second later he passed out.

1230
01:21:03,458 --> 01:21:04,492
It's been a long night.

1231
01:21:04,492 --> 01:21:05,927
Listen to me.

1232
01:21:05,927 --> 01:21:06,994
We're going to have to
take you to the doctor.

1233
01:21:06,994 --> 01:21:09,030
No. They'll just call the sheriff.

1234
01:21:09,030 --> 01:21:10,098
What are you talking about?

1235
01:21:10,098 --> 01:21:11,132
Are you guys in some kind of trouble?

1236
01:21:11,132 --> 01:21:12,533
We were, but we're find now.

1237
01:21:12,533 --> 01:21:14,057
Shelley!

1238
01:21:16,471 --> 01:21:17,605
Baby.

1239
01:21:17,605 --> 01:21:20,233
Oh, hey sweetheart.

1240
01:21:21,509 --> 01:21:23,568
I'll get you a blanket.

1241
01:21:29,384 --> 01:21:31,784
What are we going to do?

1242
01:21:33,354 --> 01:21:39,156
We're going to rest here a little bit,
and then we're going to leave.

1243
01:21:39,794 --> 01:21:42,630
We're going to leave for good, okay?

1244
01:21:42,630 --> 01:21:44,393
Yeah.

1245
01:21:46,234 --> 01:21:49,931
And we're always going to be together.

1246
01:21:51,205 --> 01:21:52,797
We are.

